## Why "Best" Lists Often Mislead

Most "best SEO companies" articles are pay-to-play. Agencies pay directory sites £500-£5,000 annually for featured listings. The "rankings" in these articles reflect marketing budgets, not service quality.

**How to spot paid placements:**

- Every listed company has a "Visit Website" affiliate link
- No negative assessments of any listed company
- The article ranks for commercial keywords but provides no evaluation methodology
- Companies are "ranked" without clear, consistent criteria
- The same companies appear across multiple supposedly independent lists

**Better sources for evaluation:**

- Google Search Console screenshots showing verifiable results
- Direct client references you can contact independently
- Independent review platforms (Google Business reviews, Trustpilot)
- Industry conference speakers demonstrating expertise publicly
- Published case studies with specific, verifiable metrics

## How to Run Your Own SEO Company Evaluation

Follow this process to identify the right provider for your business.

**Week 1 — shortlist:** Identify 5-8 potential providers through recommendations, independent research, and directory listings. Prioritise companies demonstrating expertise in your industry or market.

**Week 2 — initial conversations:** Book discovery calls with your top 5. Use the 8-point framework above. Eliminate providers that cannot answer basic methodology questions.

**Week 3 — proposal review:** Request detailed proposals from your top 3. Compare deliverables, timelines, pricing, and contract terms. Look for specificity — generic proposals indicate generic service.

**Week 4 — reference checks:** Contact references from your top 2 providers. Ask about communication quality, results accuracy, and whether the provider delivered what they promised during the sales process.

**Decision:** Choose the provider whose methodology aligns with your goals, whose pricing matches your budget, and whose references confirm they deliver on promises.

